{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887535863,"sessionID":"ses_284daec25ffeYvCPebmDHCWqiD","part":{"id":"prt_d7b254c5e001XvJkIIcs6HuBLk","messageID":"msg_d7b253f620016jbSlYLk547dhw","sessionID":"ses_284daec25ffeYvCPebmDHCWqiD","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e896fed37e394403af58ba18857871a7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-035/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-035/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-035 — client-go 类型客户端生成 Design\n2: \n3: ## AR-035 — client-go 类型客户端生成\n4: \n5: **Module**: `client-go`\n6: **Language**: Go\n7: **Size**: L\n8: **Purpose**: Generate a type-safe Kubernetes client-go library for AgentCube custom resources (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter), providing typed API access with CRUD operations, Watch mechanism, and Informer pattern support.\n9: \n10: ## Architecture\n11: \n12: ### Package Structure\n13: \n14: ```\n15: client-go/\n16: ├── clientset/\n17: │   └── versioned/\n18: │       ├── clientset.go                    # Clientset, Interface, constructors\n19: │       ├── doc.go                          # Package documentation\n20: │       ├── scheme/\n21: │       │   ├── doc.go                      # Scheme documentation\n22: │       │   └── register.go                 # Scheme / codecs for generated client\n23: │       ├── fake/\n24: │       │   ├── clientset_generated.go      # Fake clientset implementation\n25: │       │   ├── doc.go                      # Fake clientset documentation\n26: │       │   └── register.go                 # Fake scheme wiring\n27: │       └── typed/\n28: │           └── runtime/\n29: │               └── v1alpha1/\n30: │                   ├── runtime_client.go    # RuntimeV1alpha1Client, RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n31: │                   ├── agentruntime.go      # AgentRuntimeInterface, typed REST client\n32: │                   ├── codeinterpreter.go   # CodeInterpreterInterface, typed REST client\n33: │                   ├── generated_expansion.go # Expansion interfaces\n34: │                   ├── doc.go               # Documentation\n35: │                   └── fake/\n36: │                       ├── fake_runtime_client.go  # Fake runtime group client\n37: │                       ├── fake_agentruntime.go    # Fake AgentRuntime client\n38: │                       ├── fake_codeinterpreter.go # Fake CodeInterpreter client\n39: │                       └── doc.go                    # Documentation\n40: ├── informers/\n41: │   └── externalversions/\n42: │       ├── factory.go                      # SharedInformerFactory, options, Start/Shutdown/WaitForCacheSync\n43: │       ├── generic.go                      # GenericInformer, ForResource\n44: │       ├── internalinterfaces/\n45: │       │   └── factory_interfaces.go       # Small factory interface + NewInformerFunc, TweakListOptionsFunc\n46: │       └── runtime/\n47: │           ├── interface.go                # Group runtime informer accessor\n48: │           └── v1alpha1/\n49: │               ├── interface.go            # v1alpha1 informer accessors\n50: │               ├── agentruntime.go         # AgentRuntime informer + constructor\n51: │               └── codeinterpreter.go      # CodeInterpreter informer + constructor\n52: ├── listers/\n53: │   └── runtime/\n54: │       └── v1alpha1/\n55: │           ├── agentruntime.go             # AgentRuntimeLister, namespace lister\n56: │           ├── codeinterpreter.go          # CodeInterpreterLister, namespace lister\n57: │           └── expansion_generated.go     # Lister expansion interfaces\n58: ├── go.mod                                   # Go module definition\n59: ├── go.sum                                   # Go dependencies\n60: └── README.md                                # Usage documentation\n61: ```\n62: \n63: ### Component Interactions\n64: \n65: ```\n66: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n67: │                     Application / Controller                    │\n68: │                                                                  │\n69: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n70: │  │                      ClientSet                           │  │\n71: │  │  NewForConfig(cfg) → *Clientset                          │  │\n72: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n73: │                            │                                    │\n74: │                            ▼                                    │\n75: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n76: │  │              RuntimeV1alpha1Interface                    │  │\n77: │  │  clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1() → RuntimeV1alpha1Interface  │  │\n78: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n79: │                            │                                    │\n80: │              ┌─────────────┴─────────────┐                    │\n81: │              ▼                           ▼                    │\n82: │  ┌──────────────────────┐   ┌──────────────────────┐        │\n83: │  │ AgentRuntimeInterface│   │CodeInterpreterInterf │        │\n84: │  │ .AgentRuntimes(ns)   │   │.CodeInterpreters(ns) │        │\n85: │  └──────────────────────┘   └──────────────────────┘        │\n86: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n87:                             │                                    │\n88:                             │ REST API (Kubernetes API Server)  │\n89:                             ▼                                    │\n90: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n91: │                   Kubernetes API Server                        │\n92: │                                                                  │\n93: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n94: │  │     runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1               │  │\n95: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n96: │  │  │  agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh        │  │  │\n97: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n98: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n99: │  │  │  codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh     │  │  │\n100: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n101: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n102: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n103: \n104: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n105: │                SharedInformerFactory (Event-driven)             │\n106: │                                                                  │\n107: │  NewSharedInformerFactory(client, resync) → factory             │\n108: │                            │                                    │\n109: │              ┌─────────────┴─────────────┐                    │\n110: │              ▼                           ▼                    │\n111: │  ┌──────────────────────┐   ┌──────────────────────┐        │\n112: │  │ AgentRuntimeInformer │   │CodeInterpreterInfor. │        │\n113: │  │ factory.Runtime()   │   │factory.Runtime()   │        │\n114: │  │  .V1alpha1()         │   │  .V1alpha1()         │        │\n115: │  │  .AgentRuntimes()    │   │  .CodeInterpreters() │        │\n116: │  └──────────────────────┘   └──────────────────────┘        │\n117: │         │                              │                     │\n118: │         ▼                              ▼                     │\n119: │  ┌──────────────────┐      ┌──────────────────┐             │\n120: │  │ AgentRuntimeList │      │CodeInterpreterLis│             │\n121: │  │ er               │      │ ter               │             │\n122: │  └──────────────────┘      └──────────────────┘             │\n123: │                                                                  │\n124: │  Event Handlers:                                                │\n125: │  - AddFunc(obj)                                                 │\n126: │  - UpdateFunc(oldObj, newObj)                                  │\n127: │  - DeleteFunc(obj)                                              │\n128: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n129: ```\n130: \n131: ## Data Structures\n132: \n133: ### Clientset Structure\n134: \n135: **File**: `clientset/versioned/clientset.go`\n136: \n137: ```go\n138: // Interface defines the clientset interface\n139: type Interface interface {\n140:     Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n141:     RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n142: }\n143: \n144: // Clientset contains the clients for groups.\n145: type Clientset struct {\n146:     *discovery.DiscoveryClient\n147:     runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client\n148: }\n149: \n150: // NewForConfig creates a new Clientset for the given config.\n151: func NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error) {\n152:     configShallowCopy := *c\n153:     if configShallowCopy.RateLimiter == nil && configShallowCopy.QPS > 0 {\n154:         if configShallowCopy.Burst <= 0 {\n155:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"burst is required to be greater than 0 when RateLimiter is not set and QPS is set to greater than 0\")\n156:         }\n157:         configShallowCopy.RateLimiter = flowcontrol.NewTokenBucketRateLimiter(configShallowCopy.QPS, configShallowCopy.Burst)\n158:     }\n159:     var cs Clientset\n160:     var err error\n161:     cs.runtimeV1alpha1, err = runtimev1alpha1.NewForConfig(&configShallowCopy)\n162:     if err != nil {\n163:         return nil, err\n164:     }\n165:     cs.DiscoveryClient, err = discovery.NewDiscoveryClientForConfig(&configShallowCopy)\n166:     if err != nil {\n167:         return nil, err\n168:     }\n169:     return &cs, nil\n170: }\n171: \n172: // NewForConfigAndClient creates a new Clientset for the given config and http client.\n173: func NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error) {\n174:     configShallowCopy := *c\n175:     if configShallowCopy.RateLimiter == nil && configShallowCopy.QPS > 0 {\n176:         if configShallowCopy.Burst <= 0 {\n177:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"burst is required to be greater than 0 when RateLimiter is not set and QPS is set to greater than 0\")\n178:         }\n179:         configShallowCopy.RateLimiter = flowcontrol.NewTokenBucketRateLimiter(configShallowCopy.QPS, configShallowCopy.Burst)\n180:     }\n181:     var cs Clientset\n182:     var err error\n183:     cs.runtimeV1alpha1, err = runtimev1alpha1.NewForConfigAndClient(&configShallowCopy, httpClient)\n184:     if err != nil {\n185:         return nil, err\n186:     }\n187:     cs.DiscoveryClient, err = discovery.NewDiscoveryClientForConfigAndClient(&configShallowCopy, httpClient)\n188:     if err != nil {\n189:         return nil, err\n190:     }\n191:     return &cs, nil\n192: }\n193: \n194: // NewForConfigOrDie creates a new Clientset for the given config and panics if there is an error in the config.\n195: func NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *Clientset {\n196:     var cs Clientset\n197:     cs.runtimeV1alpha1 = runtimev1alpha1.NewForConfigOrDie(c)\n198:     cs.DiscoveryClient = discovery.NewDiscoveryClientForConfigOrDie(c)\n199:     return &cs\n200: }\n201: \n202: // New creates a new Clientset for the given RESTClient.\n203: func New(c rest.Interface) *Clientset {\n204:     var cs Clientset\n205:     cs.runtimeV1alpha1 = runtimev1alpha1.New(c)\n206:     cs.DiscoveryClient = discovery.NewDiscoveryClient(c)\n207:     return &cs\n208: }\n209: \n210: // RuntimeV1alpha1 retrieves the RuntimeV1alpha1Client\n211: func (c *Clientset) RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface {\n212:     return c.runtimeV1alpha1\n213: }\n214: ```\n215: \n216: ### RuntimeV1alpha1 Typed Client\n217: \n218: **File**: `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`\n219: \n220: ```go\n221: // RuntimeV1alpha1Client is used to interact with features provided by the runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh group.\n222: type RuntimeV1alpha1Client struct {\n223:     restClient rest.Interface\n224: }\n225: \n226: // NewForConfig creates a new RuntimeV1alpha1Client for the given config.\n227: func NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*RuntimeV1alpha1Client, error) {\n228:     config := *c\n229:     if err := setConfigDefaults(&config); err != nil {\n230:         return nil, err\n231:     }\n232:     client, err := rest.RESTClientFor(&config)\n233:     if err != nil {\n234:         return nil, err\n235:     }\n236:     return &RuntimeV1alpha1Client{client}, nil\n237: }\n238: \n239: // NewForConfigAndClient creates a new RuntimeV1alpha1Client for the given config and HTTP client.\n240: func NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*RuntimeV1alpha1Client, error) {\n241:     config := *c\n242:     if err := setConfigDefaults(&config); err != nil {\n243:         return nil, err\n244:     }\n245:     client, err := rest.RESTClientForConfigAndClient(&config, httpClient)\n246:     if err != nil {\n247:         return nil, err\n248:     }\n249:     return &RuntimeV1alpha1Client{client}, nil\n250: }\n251: \n252: // NewForConfigOrDie creates a new RuntimeV1alpha1Client for the given config and panics if there is an error in the config.\n253: func NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *RuntimeV1alpha1Client {\n254:     client, err := NewForConfig(c)\n255:     if err != nil {\n256:         panic(err)\n257:     }\n258:     return client\n259: }\n260: \n261: // New creates a new RuntimeV1alpha1Client for the given RESTClient.\n262: func New(c rest.Interface) *RuntimeV1alpha1Client {\n263:     return &RuntimeV1alpha1Client{c}\n264: }\n265: \n266: // setConfigDefaults sets default values on the provided client config.\n267: func setConfigDefaults(config *rest.Config) error {\n268:     gvk := schema.GroupVersionKind{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}\n269:     config.GroupVersion = &schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}\n270:     config.APIPath = \"/apis\"\n271:     config.NegotiatedSerializer = scheme.Codecs.WithoutConversion()\n272:     if config.UserAgent == \"\" {\n273:         config.UserAgent = rest.DefaultKubernetesUserAgent()\n274:     }\n275:     return nil\n276: }\n277: \n278: // RESTClient returns a RESTClient that is used to communicate with API server by this client implementation.\n279: func (c *RuntimeV1alpha1Client) RESTClient() rest.Interface {\n280:     if c == nil {\n281:         return nil\n282:     }\n283:     return c.restClient\n284: }\n285: ```\n286: \n287: ### AgentRuntime Interface\n288: \n289: **File**: `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n290: \n291: ```go\n292: // AgentRuntimesGetter has a method to return a AgentRuntimeInterface.\n293: type AgentRuntimesGetter interface {\n294:     AgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface\n295: }\n296: \n297: // AgentRuntimeInterface has methods to work with AgentRuntime resources.\n298: type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n299:     Create(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n300:     Update(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n301:     UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n302:     Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n303:     DeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n304:     Get(ctx contex