{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887872697,"sessionID":"ses_284daec25ffeYvCPebmDHCWqiD","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2a6fbd001LA5Ld1GAkxvek0","messageID":"msg_d7b29e12a001qdxFoh2PdAJlGV","sessionID":"ses_284daec25ffeYvCPebmDHCWqiD","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-3187260a907d42108f4ea268482b55ad","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AgentCube client-go\n\nType-safe Kubernetes client library for AgentCube custom resources (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter).\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\ngo get github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\n```\n\n## Overview\n\nThis client-go library provides a type-safe, idiomatic Go client for managing AgentCube custom resources:\n\n- **AgentRuntime**: Manages agent runtime configurations and sandbox orchestration\n- **CodeInterpreter**: Manages code execution environments\n\nThe library includes:\n- ClientSet for typed REST clients\n- Informers for event-driven workflows\n- Listers for efficient read-only operations\n\n## Quick Start\n\n### Create ClientSet\n\n```go\npackage main\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"fmt\"\n    \"time\"\n    \n    metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n    clientset \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n    runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n)\n\nfunc main() {\n    // Load kubeconfig\n    config, err := clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", \"/path/to/kubeconfig\")\n    if err != nil {\n        panic(err.Error())\n    }\n    \n    // Create clientset\n    client, err := clientset.NewForConfig(config)\n    if err != nil {\n        panic(err.Error())\n    }\n    \n    // Use client...\n    fmt.Println(\"Client created successfully!\")\n}\n```\n\n### Create AgentRuntime\n\n```go\nagentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n    ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n        Name:      \"my-agent\",\n        Namespace: \"default\",\n    },\n    Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n        MaxSessionDuration: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 8 * time.Hour},\n        SessionTimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n        PodTemplate: &runtimev1alpha1.SandboxTemplate{\n            Spec: runtimev1alpha1.SandboxPodSpec{\n                Containers: []runtimev1alpha1.SandboxContainer{\n                    {\n                        Name:  \"agent\",\n                        Image: \"agent-image:latest\",\n                        Ports: []runtimev1alpha1.SandboxContainerPort{\n                            {\n                                ContainerPort: 8080,\n                                Protocol:      \"HTTP\",\n                            },\n                        },\n                    },\n                },\n            },\n        },\n    },\n}\n\ncreated, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Create(context.TODO(), agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})\nif err != nil {\n    panic(err.Error())\n}\n\nfmt.Printf(\"Created AgentRuntime: %s\\n\", created.Name)\n```\n\n### Get AgentRuntime\n\n```go\nagentRuntime, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Get(context.TODO(), \"my-agent\", metav1.GetOptions{})\nif err != nil {\n    panic(err.Error())\n}\n\nfmt.Printf(\"AgentRuntime: %+v\\n\", agentRuntime)\n```\n\n### Update AgentRuntime\n\n```go\nagentRuntime, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Get(context.TODO(), \"my-agent\", metav1.GetOptions{})\nif err != nil {\n    panic(err.Error())\n}\n\nagentRuntime.Spec.MaxSessionDuration = &metav1.Duration{Duration: 12 * time.Hour}\n\nupdated, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Update(context.TODO(), agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\nif err != nil {\n    panic(err.Error())\n}\n\nfmt.Printf(\"Updated AgentRuntime: %s\\n\", updated.Name)\n```\n\n### Update AgentRuntime Status\n\n```go\nagentRuntime, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Get(context.TODO(), \"my-agent\", metav1.GetOptions{})\nif err != nil {\n    panic(err.Error())\n}\n\nagentRuntime.Status.ObservedGeneration = agentRuntime.Generation\nagentRuntime.Status.Conditions = []metav1.Condition{\n    {\n        Type:               \"Ready\",\n        Status:             metav1.ConditionTrue,\n        LastTransitionTime: metav1.Now(),\n        Reason:             \"Available\",\n        Message:            \"AgentRuntime is ready\",\n    },\n}\n\nupdated, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").UpdateStatus(context.TODO(), agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\nif err != nil {\n    panic(err.Error())\n}\n\nfmt.Printf(\"Updated status: %s\\n\", updated.Name)\n```\n\n### List AgentRuntimes\n\n```go\nlist, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").List(context.TODO(), metav1.ListOptions{})\nif err != nil {\n    panic(err.Error())\n}\n\nfmt.Printf(\"Found %d AgentRuntimes\\n\", len(list.Items))\nfor _, ar := range list.Items {\n    fmt.Printf(\"- %s\\n\", ar.Name)\n}\n```\n\n### Watch AgentRuntimes\n\n```go\nwatcher, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Watch(context.TODO(), metav1.ListOptions{})\nif err != nil {\n    panic(err.Error())\n}\ndefer watcher.Stop()\n\nfor event := range watcher.ResultChan() {\n    switch event.Type {\n    case watch.Added:\n        ar := event.Object.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n        fmt.Printf(\"Added: %s\\n\", ar.Name)\n    case watch.Modified:\n        ar := event.Object.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n        fmt.Printf(\"Modified: %s\\n\", ar.Name)\n    case watch.Deleted:\n        ar := event.Object.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n        fmt.Printf(\"Deleted: %s\\n\", ar.Name)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Delete AgentRuntime\n\n```go\nerr := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Delete(context.TODO(), \"my-agent\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})\nif err != nil {\n    panic(err.Error())\n}\n\nfmt.Printf(\"Deleted AgentRuntime: my-agent\\n\")\n```\n\n### Create CodeInterpreter\n\n```go\ncodeInterpreter := &runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{\n    ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n        Name:      \"python-interpreter\",\n        Namespace: \"default\",\n    },\n    Spec: runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterSpec{\n        Image:   \"python:3.11-slim\",\n        Runtime: \"python\",\n        Timeout: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 5 * time.Minute},\n    },\n}\n\ncreated, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(\"default\").Create(context.TODO(), codeInterpreter, metav1.CreateOptions{})\nif err != nil {\n    panic(err.Error())\n}\n\nfmt.Printf(\"Created CodeInterpreter: %s\\n\", created.Name)\n```\n\n## Using Informers\n\nInformers provide efficient event-driven workflows by maintaining a local cache and watching for changes.\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"fmt\"\n    \"time\"\n    \n    \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/wait\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/util/workqueue\"\n    \n    clientset \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n    informers \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/informers/externalversions\"\n)\n\nfunc main() {\n    // Create clientset\n    config, _ := clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", \"/path/to/kubeconfig\")\n    client, _ := clientset.NewForConfig(config)\n    \n    // Create informer factory with 10 minute resync\n    factory := informers.NewSharedInformerFactory(client, 10*time.Minute)\n    \n    // Get AgentRuntime informer\n    agentRuntimeInformer := factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes()\n    \n    // Set up event handlers\n    agentRuntimeInformer.Informer().AddEventHandler(cache.ResourceEventHandlerFuncs{\n        AddFunc: func(obj interface{}) {\n            ar := obj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n            fmt.Printf(\"AgentRuntime added: %s\\n\", ar.Name)\n        },\n        UpdateFunc: func(oldObj, newObj interface{}) {\n            oldAr := oldObj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n            newAr := newObj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n            if oldAr.ResourceVersion != newAr.ResourceVersion {\n                fmt.Printf(\"AgentRuntime updated: %s\\n\", newAr.Name)\n            }\n        },\n        DeleteFunc: func(obj interface{}) {\n            ar := obj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n            fmt.Printf(\"AgentRuntime deleted: %s\\n\", ar.Name)\n        },\n    })\n    \n    // Start informers\n    stopCh := make(chan struct{})\n    defer close(stopCh)\n    \n    factory.Start(stopCh)\n    \n    // Wait for cache sync\n    if !cache.WaitForCacheSync(stopCh, agentRuntimeInformer.Informer().HasSynced) {\n        panic(\"Timed out waiting for caches to sync\")\n    }\n    \n    // Use lister for efficient read-only access\n    lister := agentRuntimeInformer.Lister()\n    agentRuntimes, err := lister.List(labels.Everything())\n    if err != nil {\n        panic(err.Error())\n    }\n    \n    fmt.Printf(\"Found %d AgentRuntimes in cache\\n\", len(agentRuntimes))\n    \n    // Keep running\n    wait.Until(func() {\n        time.Sleep(time.Second)\n    }, time.Second, stopCh)\n}\n```\n\n## Best Practices\n\n### Context Usage\n\nAlways provide context to client methods for proper cancellation and timeout control:\n\n```go\nctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\ndefer cancel()\n\nagentRuntime, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Get(ctx, \"my-agent\", metav1.GetOptions{})\n```\n\n### Error Handling\n\nHandle errors appropriately using Kubernetes error utilities:\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n)\n\nagentRuntime, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Get(ctx, \"my-agent\", metav1.GetOptions{})\nif errors.IsNotFound(err) {\n    fmt.Println(\"AgentRuntime not found\")\n} else if err != nil {\n    panic(err.Error())\n}\n```\n\n### Resource Cleanup\n\nAlways stop informers when done to prevent goroutine leaks:\n\n```go\nstopCh := make(chan struct{})\ndefer close(stopCh)\n\nfactory.Start(stopCh)\n\n// When done, close stopCh to clean up\n```\n\n### Retry Logic\n\nImplement retry logic for transient failures:\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/util/retry\"\n)\n\nerr := retry.RetryOnConflict(retry.DefaultRetry, func() error {\n    agentRuntime, err := client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Get(ctx, \"my-agent\", metav1.GetOptions{})\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    \n    agentRuntime.Spec.MaxSessionDuration = &metav1.Duration{Duration: 12 * time.Hour}\n    \n    _, err = client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Update(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n    return err\n})\n```\n\n## API Reference\n\n### ClientSet\n\n`clientset.Interface` provides access to all API groups:\n\n```go\ntype Interface interface {\n    Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n    RuntimeV1alpha1() RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n}\n```\n\n### AgentRuntime Interface\n\n```go\ntype AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n    Create(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Update(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n    Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*v1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n    Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n    Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n}\n```\n\n### CodeInterpreter Interface\n\n```go\ntype CodeInterpreterInterface interface {\n    Create(ctx context.Context, codeInterpreter *v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    Update(ctx context.Context, codeInterpreter *v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, codeInterpreter *v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n    Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n    List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*v1alpha1.CodeInterpreterList, error)\n    Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n    Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n}\n```\n\n## Contributing\n\nSee [CONTRIBUTING.md](../CONTRIBUTING.md) for guidelines.\n\n## License\n\nApache 2.0 - See [LICENSE](../LICENSE) for details.","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli-bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/client-go/README.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/codeinterpreter.go\">\nERROR [63:7] undefined: statusConditionsEqual\nERROR [106:6] undefined: statusConditionsEqual\nERROR [173:2] declared and not used: logger\nERROR [242:5] undefined: podSpecsEqual\nERROR [267:29] undefined: convertEnvVars\nERROR [274:25] undefined: convertResources\nERROR [326:6] undefined: statusConditionsEqual\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/gc/collecto